data.name: DescriptionNumberFormatE

data.name: DescriptionNumberFormatD

The precision specifier indicates the minimum number of digits desired in the resulting string. If required, the number is padded with zeros to its left to produce the number of digits given by the precision specifier.

data.name: DescriptionNumberFormatN
data.value: The number is converted to a string of the form '-d,ddd,ddd.ddd…', where each 'd' indicates a digit (0-9). The string starts with a minus sign if the number is negative.
